usehold member willing to do unskilled manual work at the notified wage rate is eligible.\\\"},{\\\"question\\\":\\\"What is the guaranteed number of days of employment?\\\",\\\"answer\\\":\\\"The Act guarantees 100 days of employment per household per financial year.\\\"}],\\\"relatedStories\\\":[{\\\"slug\\\":\\\"digital-payments-boom\\\",\\\"headline\\\":\\\"Digital Payments in Rural India\\\",\\\"summary\\\":\\\"UPI's role in rural financial inclusion.\\\",\\\"publishedAt\\\":\\\"2026-06-12T08:00:00Z\\\",\\\"readingTime\\\":8,\\\"evidenceScore\\\":88,\\\"category\\\":\\\"technology\\\"}],\\\"relatedEntities\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"ministry-of-rural-development\\\",\\\"slug\\\":\\\"ministry-of-rural-development\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Ministry of Rural Development\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"organization\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Nodal ministry for MGNREGA implementation.\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"india\\\",\\\"slug\\\":\\\"india\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"India\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"country\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Republic of India.\\\"}],\\\"relatedTopicIds\\\":[\\\"economy\\\",\\\"policy\\\",\\\"agriculture\\\",\\\"employment\\\"],\\\"relatedEntityIds\\\":[\\\"ministry-of-rural-development\\\",\\\"india\\\"]},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"digital-payments-boom\\\",\\\"slug\\\":\\\"digital-payments-boom\\\",\\\"headline\\\":\\\"Digital Payments in Rural India: UPI's Unseen Revolution\\\",\\\"summary\\\":\\\"How UPI transformed rural financial inclusion, with transaction volumes growing 400% in three years.\\\",\\\"heroImage\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"publishedAt\\\":\\\"2026-06-12T08:00:00Z\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2026-06-12T08:00:00Z\\\",\\\"readingTime\\\":8,\\\"author\\\":{\\\"name\\\":\\\"The Breakdown Editorial\\\"},\\\"evidenceScore\\\":88,\\\"category\\\":\\\"technology\\\",\\\"tags\\\":[\\\"UPI\\\",\\\"digital payments\\\",\\\"rural India\\\",\\\"fintech\\\",\\\"NPCI\\\"],\\\"keyPoints\\\":[\\\"UPI transactions in rural areas grew 400% since 2023\\\",\\\"Feature phone-based UPI drove adoption in remote areas\\\",\\\"18 crore feature phone UPI users as of 2026\\\"],\\\"timeline\\\":[{\\\"date\\\":\\\"2016-04-11\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"UPI Launched\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"NPCI launches Unified Payments Interface.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"NPCI\\\"},{\\\"date\\\":\\\"2020-01-01\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"UPI 2.0 Released\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Feature phone support added via USSD 2.0.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"NPCI\\\"},{\\\"date\\\":\\\"2023-06-01\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Rural UPI Crosses ₹5L Cr\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Annual rural UPI transactions cross ₹5 lakh crore.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"NPCI Annual Report\\\"},{\\\"date\\\":\\\"2026-03-01\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Rural UPI at ₹12L Cr\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Rural UPI transactions reach ₹12 lakh crore annually.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"The Breakdown Analysis\\\"}],\\\"facts\\\":[{\\\"value\\\":\\\"₹12 lakh crore\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Rural UPI Transactions (2025-26)\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"NPCI\\\"},{\\\"value\\\":\\\"18 crore\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Feature Phone UPI Users\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"NPCI Annual Report\\\"},{\\\"value\\\":\\\"63%\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Year-on-Year Growth\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"NPCI\\\"}],\\\"claims\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"claim-8jto0j\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"UPI has eliminated the urban-rural digital payments divide.\\\",\\\"confidence\\\":75,\\\"status\\\":\\\"moderate\\\",\\\"sources\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Industry Report 2025\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"group\\\":\\\"report\\\"}],\\\"supportingEvidence\\\":[\\\"Urban transactions still account for 68% of total UPI volume.\\\"]}],\\\"sources\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"NPCI Annual Report 2025-26\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://npci.org.in\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"government\\\",\\\"tier\\\":1}],\\\"charts\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Rural UPI Transaction Growth (₹L Cr)\\\",\\\"data\\\":[{\\\"label\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"},{\\\"label\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"},{\\\"label\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"},{\\\"label\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"},{\\\"label\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"},{\\\"label\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"}],\\\"xKey\\\":\\\"label\\\",\\\"yKey\\\":\\\"value\\\"}],\\\"faq\\\":[{\\\"question\\\":\\\"How does UPI work on feature phones?\\\",\\\"answer\\\":\\\"UPI works on feature phones via USSD codes (*99#) and NPCI's UPI123Pay service.\\\"}],\\\"relatedStories\\\":[{\\\"slug\\\":\\\"mgnrega-reform\\\",\\\"headline\\\":\\\"MGNREGA Completes 20 Years\\\",\\\"summary\\\":\\\"Data-driven assessment.\\\",\\\"publishedAt\\\":\\\"2026-06-15T10:00:00Z\\\",\\\"readingTime\\\":12,\\\"evidenceScore\\\":92,\\\"category\\\":\\\"economy\\\"}],\\\"relatedEntities\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"npci\\\",\\\"slug\\\":\\\"npci\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"NPCI\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"organization\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"National Payments Corporation of India.\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rbi\\\",\\\"slug\\\":\\\"rbi\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Reserve Bank of India\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"organization\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"India's central bank.\\\"}],\\\"relatedTopicIds\\\":[\\\"economy\\\",\\\"technology\\\",\\\"digital-payments\\\",\\\"agriculture\\\"],\\\"relatedEntityIds\\\":[\\\"npci\\\",\\\"rbi\\\"]},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"pm-fasal-bima-claims\\\",\\\"slug\\\":\\\"pm-fasal-bima-claims\\\",\\\"headline\\\":\\\"PM Fasal Bima Yojana: The Claims That Never Reached Farmers\\\",\\\"summary\\\":\\\"Investigation into delayed and unpaid crop insurance claims across six states.\\\",\\\"heroImage\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"publishedAt\\\":\\\"2026-06-05T06:00:00Z\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2026-06-05T06:00:00Z\\\",\\\"readingTime\\\":15,\\\"author\\\":{\\\"name\\\":\\\"The Breakdown Editorial\\\"},\\\"evidenceScore\\\":97,\\\"category\\\":\\\"policy\\\",\\\"tags\\\":[\\\"crop insurance\\\",\\\"agriculture\\\",\\\"farmer welfare\\\",\\\"PMFBY\\\"],\\\"keyPoints\\\":[\\\"Over 40% of claims delayed beyond 60 days in 4 states\\\",\\\"Farmers in Maharashtra and Karnataka worst affected\\\",\\\"Claims settlement ratio declined from 85% to 63% in 3 years\\\"],\\\"timeline\\\":[{\\\"date\\\":\\\"2016-01-13\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"PMFBY Launched\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"PM Fasal Bima Yojana launched to replace existing crop insurance schemes.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"PIB\\\"},{\\\"date\\\":\\\"2020-02-01\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Revised Guidelines\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Government revises PMFBY guidelines to speed up claims.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"Ministry of Agriculture\\\"},{\\\"date\\\":\\\"2024-08-15\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"CAG Report Flags Delays\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"CAG report highlights systemic delays in claim settlement.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"CAG Report\\\"},{\\\"date\\\":\\\"2026-04-01\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Investigation Published\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"The Breakdown publishes investigation across 6 states.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"The Breakdown\\\"}],\\\"facts\\\":[{\\\"value\\\":\\\"42%\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Claims Pending Beyond 60 Days\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"State Govt Data\\\"},{\\\"value\\\":\\\"1.2 crore\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Farmers Affected\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"CAG Report 2024\\\"},{\\\"value\\\":\\\"₹29,000 crore\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Total Premium Collected\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"Annual Report\\\"},{\\\"value\\\":\\\"₹13,400 crore\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Claims Actually Paid\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"Annual Report\\\"}],\\\"claims\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"claim-curt1f\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Insurance companies are deliberately delaying claim settlements to earn interest.\\\",\\\"confidence\\\":60,\\\"status\\\":\\\"moderate\\\",\\\"sources\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Farmer Unions\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"group\\\":\\\"report\\\"}],\\\"supportingEvidence\\\":[\\\"While delays are documented, intent cannot be verified without regulatory investigation.\\\"]},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"claim-dfmw9f\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"States are not contributing their share of premium on time.\\\",\\\"confidence\\\":85,\\\"status\\\":\\\"verified\\\",\\\"sources\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Union Agriculture Ministry\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"group\\\":\\\"report\\\"}],\\\"supportingEvidence\\\":[\\\"4 states have pending premium contributions exceeding ₹2,000 crore.\\\"]}],\\\"sources\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"CAG Report on PMFBY 2024\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://cag.gov.in\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"government\\\",\\\"tier\\\":1},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"State Government Data Compilation\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"government\\\",\\\"tier\\\":2}],\\\"charts\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Claims Settlement Ratio by State (2025-26)\\\",\\\"data\\\":[{\\\"label\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"},{\\\"label\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"},{\\\"label\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"},{\\\"label\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"},{\\\"label\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"},{\\\"label\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"}],\\\"xKey\\\":\\\"label\\\",\\\"yKey\\\":\\\"value\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Claims Settlement Trend\\\",\\\"data\\\":[{\\\"label\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"},{\\\"label\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"},{\\\"label\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"},{\\\"label\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"},{\\\"label\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"}],\\\"xKey\\\":\\\"label\\\",\\\"yKey\\\":\\\"value\\\"}],\\\"faq\\\":[{\\\"question\\\":\\\"What is the claim settlement timeline under PMFBY?\\\",\\\"answer\\\":\\\"Claims must be settled within 60 days of harvest. Delays beyond this attract penal interest at 12% per annum.\\\"},{\\\"question\\\":\\\"Who implements PMFBY?\\\",\\\"answer\\\":\\\"The scheme is implemented by empaneled insurance companies, with premium shared by farmer, central, and state governments.\\\"}],\\\"relatedStories\\\":[{\\\"slug\\\":\\\"mgnrega-reform\\\",\\\"headline\\\":\\\"MGNREGA Completes 20 Years\\\",\\\"summary\\\":\\\"Data-driven assessment.\\\",\\\"publishedAt\\\":\\\"2026-06-15T10:00:00Z\\\",\\\"readingTime\\\":12,\\\"evidenceScore\\\":92,\\\"category\\\":\\\"economy\\\"}],\\\"relatedEntities\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"ministry-of-agriculture\\\",\\\"slug\\\":\\\"ministry-of-agriculture\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Ministry of Agriculture\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"organization\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Nodal ministry.\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"india\\\",\\\"slug\\\":\\\"india\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"India\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"country\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"cag\\\",\\\"slug\\\":\\\"cag\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Comptroller and Auditor General\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"organization\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Supreme audit institution.\\\"}],\\\"relatedTopicIds\\\":[\\\"policy\\\",\\\"agriculture\\\"],\\\"relatedEntityIds\\\":[\\\"ministry-of-agriculture\\\",\\\"india\\\",\\\"cag\\\"]}]}]}]\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"1b:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L22\\\",null,{\\\"as\\\":\\\"div\\\",\\\"delay\\\":200,\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L2b\\\",null,{\\\"fixes\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"fix-mgnrega-reform\\\",\\\"slug\\\":\\\"fix-mgnrega-reform\\\",\\\"storySlug\\\":\\\"fix-mgnrega-reform\\\",\\\"headline\\\":\\\"Fixing MGNREGA: 5 Reforms to Make Rural Employment Work\\\",\\\"summary\\\":\\\"Despite 20 years of operation, MGNREGA wage rates are indexed to CPI-AL but revisions are delayed by 6-18 months. In 12 of 28 states, scheme wages fall below prevailing market rates, reducing the sche\\\",\\\"publishedAt\\\":\\\"2026-06-16T10:00:00Z\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2026-06-16T10:00:00Z\\\",\\\"readingTime\\\":5,\\\"author\\\":{\\\"name\\\":\\\"The Breakdown Editorial\\\"},\\\"evidenceScore\\\":80,\\\"tags\\\":[],\\\"problem\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Despite 20 years of operation, MGNREGA wage rates are indexed to CPI-AL but revisions are delayed by\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Despite 20 years of operation, MGNREGA wage rates are indexed to CPI-AL but revisions are delayed by 6-18 months. In 12 of 28 states, scheme wages fall below prevailing market rates, reducing the scheme's effectiveness as both a safety net and a wage floor.\\\"},\\\"whoIsAffected\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Who Is Affected\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"\\\"},\\\"rootCauses\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Root Causes\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Three structural issues: (1) Wage indexation linked to CPI-AL lacks automatic adjustment mechanism, causing erosion of real wages. (2) Fund flow from Centre to districts takes 45-90 days, delaying wage payments. (3) Only 42% of created assets are maintained beyond 3 years.\\\"},\\\"existingSolutions\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Direct Benefit Transfer (DBT)\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Wage payments directly to bank accounts was introduced in 2017-18, reducing leakage but not delays.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"active\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"MoRD Annual Report\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Social Audit System\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Village-level social audits mandated in 2010 to improve transparency and asset quality.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"active\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"CAG Report 2024\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"e-FMS (Electronic Fund Management System)\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Launched 2015 to track fund flows digitally, but state-level bottlenecks persist.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"active\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"NREGA MIS\\\"}],\\\"evidence\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Evidence\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"\\\"},\\\"stakeholders\\\":[],\\\"globalExamples\\\":[{\\\"country\\\":\\\"Brazil\\\",\\\"policy\\\":\\\"Bolsa Família conditional cash transfer\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Reduced poverty by 15% in 5 years with lower administrative costs.\\\",\\\"outcome\\\":\\\"Reduced poverty by 15% in 5 years with lower administrative costs.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"World Bank\\\"},{\\\"country\\\":\\\"Ethiopia\\\",\\\"policy\\\":\\\"Productive Safety Net Programme (PSNP)\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Asset retention rate of 78% after 5 years vs 42% in India.\\\",\\\"outcome\\\":\\\"Asset retention rate of 78% after 5 years vs 42% in India.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"IFPRI Study\\\"},{\\\"country\\\":\\\"South Africa\\\",\\\"policy\\\":\\\"Community Work Programme (CWP)\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Asset quality scores improved 34% in pilot districts.\\\",\\\"outcome\\\":\\\"Asset quality scores improved 34% in pilot districts.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"DPME South Africa\\\"}],\\\"recommendedActions\\\":[{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Automatic wage indexation\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"MoRD, Ministry of Finance\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Real-time fund flow tracking\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"MoRD, NeGD, States\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Asset maintenance mandate\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"MoRD, Gram Panchayats\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Performance-linked wage bonus\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"MoRD, ISRO, State Govts\\\"]}],\\\"citizenActions\\\":[{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Demand social audits\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Form worker collectives\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Use MNREGA MIS app\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[]}],\\\"governmentActions\\\":[{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Pass MGNREGA Amendment Bill\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"high\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Government\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Clear pending state share\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"high\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Government\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Integrate with GIS platform\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"high\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Government\\\"]}],\\\"metricsToTrack\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Average wage payment delay\\\",\\\"currentValue\\\":\\\"45 days\\\",\\\"targetValue\\\":\\\"\\u003c15 days\\\",\\\"dataSource\\\":\\\"NREGA MIS\\\",\\\"updateFrequency\\\":\\\"\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Asset maintenance rate\\\",\\\"currentValue\\\":\\\"42%\\\",\\\"targetValue\\\":\\\"\\u003e70%\\\",\\\"dataSource\\\":\\\"CAG/Social Audits\\\",\\\"updateFrequency\\\":\\\"\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Real wage growth\\\",\\\"currentValue\\\":\\\"-8% (since 2018)\\\",\\\"targetValue\\\":\\\"\\u003e0% (positive)\\\",\\\"dataSource\\\":\\\"CPI-AL vs Wage\\\",\\\"updateFrequency\\\":\\\"\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Women participation rate\\\",\\\"currentValue\\\":\\\"55.3%\\\",\\\"targetValue\\\":\\\"60%\\\",\\\"dataSource\\\":\\\"MoRD Dashboard\\\",\\\"updateFrequency\\\":\\\"\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Fund flow time (Centre to GP)\\\",\\\"currentValue\\\":\\\"45-90 days\\\",\\\"targetValue\\\":\\\"\\u003c21 days\\\",\\\"dataSource\\\":\\\"e-FMS Tracking\\\",\\\"updateFrequency\\\":\\\"\\\"}],\\\"relatedStories\\\":[],\\\"relatedEntities\\\":[]},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"fix-pmfby-claims\\\",\\\"slug\\\":\\\"fix-pmfby-claims\\\",\\\"storySlug\\\":\\\"fix-pmfby-claims\\\",\\\"headline\\\":\\\"The Fix: How to Fix Crop Insurance in India\\\",\\\"summary\\\":\\\"The PM Fasal Bima Yojana (PMFBY), India's flagship crop insurance scheme, has a systemic claims settlement crisis. Our investigation across 6 states found 42% of claims delayed beyond the mandated 60-\\\",\\\"publishedAt\\\":\\\"2026-06-06T06:00:00Z\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2026-06-06T06:00:00Z\\\",\\\"readingTime\\\":5,\\\"author\\\":{\\\"name\\\":\\\"The Breakdown Editorial\\\"},\\\"evidenceScore\\\":80,\\\"tags\\\":[],\\\"problem\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"The PM Fasal Bima Yojana (PMFBY), India's flagship crop insurance scheme, has a systemic claims sett\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"The PM Fasal Bima Yojana (PMFBY), India's flagship crop insurance scheme, has a systemic claims settlement crisis. Our investigation across 6 states found 42% of claims delayed beyond the mandated 60-day period, leaving 1.2 crore farmers in financial distress.\\\"},\\\"whoIsAffected\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Who Is Affected\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"\\\"},\\\"rootCauses\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Root Causes\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Three systemic failures: (1) Insurance companies have discretion to delay claims with minimal penalties. (2) 4 states have pending premium contributions exceeding ₹2,000 crore. (3) Loss assessment relies on manual crop cutting experiments (CCEs) that take 60-90 days, far beyond the 30-day ideal.\\\"},\\\"existingSolutions\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"PMFBY 2.0 Guidelines (2020)\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Revised guidelines mandated 60-day claim settlement and penal interest of 12% p.a. for delays.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"active\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"Ministry of Agriculture\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Crop Insurance Portal\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Centralised portal for claim tracking launched in 2021, but adoption is low and data is not real-time.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"active\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"PMFBY Website\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"MahaSBY (State-level)\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Maharashtra's own crop insurance scheme with simplified claim process, 30-day settlement guarantee.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"active\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"Maharashtra Govt\\\"}],\\\"evidence\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Evidence\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"\\\"},\\\"stakeholders\\\":[],\\\"globalExamples\\\":[{\\\"country\\\":\\\"USA\\\",\\\"policy\\\":\\\"Federal Crop Insurance Act (FCIP)\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"90% of claims settled within 30 days, 99% within 60 days.\\\",\\\"outcome\\\":\\\"90% of claims settled within 30 days, 99% within 60 days.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"USDA RMA\\\"},{\\\"country\\\":\\\"China\\\",\\\"policy\\\":\\\"Centralised Crop Insurance Scheme\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Claim settlement ratio of 92%, average payout time 18 days.\\\",\\\"outcome\\\":\\\"Claim settlement ratio of 92%, average payout time 18 days.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"World Bank Agricultural Insurance\\\"},{\\\"country\\\":\\\"Kenya\\\",\\\"policy\\\":\\\"Kilimo Salama (index-based insurance)\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"98% farmer satisfaction, zero claims disputes.\\\",\\\"outcome\\\":\\\"98% farmer satisfaction, zero claims disputes.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"Syngenta Foundation\\\"}],\\\"recommendedActions\\\":[{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Mandate satellite-based loss assessment\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Ministry of Agriculture, ISRO, IRDAI\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Auto-trigger claims for insured areas\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Ministry of Agriculture, Insurance Companies, State Govts\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Deduct state premium from central transfers\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Ministry of Finance, Ministry of Agriculture\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Create insurance company blacklist\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"IRDAI, Ministry of Agriculture\\\"]}],\\\"citizenActions\\\":[{\\\"title\\\":\\\"File complaints on PMFBY portal\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Form farmer claim support groups\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[]}],\\\"governmentActions\\\":[{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Pass Crop Insurance (Reform) Bill\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"high\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Government\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Clear pending state premiums immediately\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"high\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Government\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Launch NAIP (National Agricultural Insurance Platform)\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"high\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Government\\\"]}],\\\"metricsToTrack\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Claim settlement ratio\\\",\\\"currentValue\\\":\\\"63%\\\",\\\"targetValue\\\":\\\"\\u003e90%\\\",\\\"dataSource\\\":\\\"PMFBY Dashboard\\\",\\\"updateFrequency\\\":\\\"\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Average claim settlement time\\\",\\\"currentValue\\\":\\\"72 days\\\",\\\"targetValue\\\":\\\"\\u003c30 days\\\",\\\"dataSource\\\":\\\"PMFBY MIS\\\",\\\"updateFrequency\\\":\\\"\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Satellite-based assessments\\\",\\\"currentValue\\\":\\\"5% of total\\\",\\\"targetValue\\\":\\\"\\u003e50%\\\",\\\"dataSource\\\":\\\"ISRO/NDVI\\\",\\\"updateFrequency\\\":\\\"\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"States with auto-deduction enabled\\\",\\\"currentValue\\\":\\\"0\\\",\\\"targetValue\\\":\\\"All states\\\",\\\"dataSource\\\":\\\"Finance Commission\\\",\\\"updateFrequency\\\":\\\"\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Penal interest paid to farmers\\\",\\\"currentValue\\\":\\\"Unknown\\\",\\\"targetValue\\\":\\\"Tracked and published\\\",\\\"dataSource\\\":\\\"IRDAI\\\",\\\"updateFrequency\\\":\\\"\\\"}],\\\"relatedStories\\\":[],\\\"relatedEntities\\\":[]},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"fix-air-pollution\\\",\\\"slug\\\":\\\"fix-air-pollution\\\",\\\"storySlug\\\":\\\"fix-air-pollution\\\",\\\"headline\\\":\\\"Fixing India's Air Pollution: A Multi-Sector Action Plan\\\",\\\"summary\\\":\\\"Despite the National Clean Air Programme (NCAP) targeting 40% reduction in PM2.5 by 2026, 132 of 141 monitored cities have failed to meet air quality standards. Sources vary by region: vehicular emiss\\\",\\\"publishedAt\\\":\\\"2026-06-10T10:00:00Z\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2026-06-10T10:00:00Z\\\",\\\"readingTime\\\":5,\\\"author\\\":{\\\"name\\\":\\\"The Breakdown Editorial\\\"},\\\"evidenceScore\\\":80,\\\"tags\\\":[],\\\"problem\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Despite the National Clean Air Programme (NCAP) targeting 40% reduction in PM2.5 by 2026, 132 of 141\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Despite the National Clean Air Programme (NCAP) targeting 40% reduction in PM2.5 by 2026, 132 of 141 monitored cities have failed to meet air quality standards. Sources vary by region: vehicular emissions dominate in cities, crop stubble burning in the Indo-Gangetic plains, industrial coal in eastern clusters, and household biomass in rural areas.\\\"},\\\"whoIsAffected\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Who Is Affected\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"\\\"},\\\"rootCauses\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Root Causes\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Seven interconnected drivers: (1) coal-dependent power generation, (2) 26% of vehicles exceeding emission norms, (3) stubble burning from 5 million farms, (4) 50% of industrial units lacking pollution control, (5) construction dust unregulated, (6) 40% of households using solid cooking fuels, (7) weak inter-state coordination on airshed management.\\\"},\\\"existingSolutions\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"National Clean Air Programme\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Targets 40% reduction in PM2.5 by 2026 across 141 non-attainment cities.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"active\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"MoEFCC\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"BS-VI Emission Norms\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Jump from BS-IV to BS-VI since 2020 for all vehicles.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"active\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Graded Response Action Plan\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Emergency measures during severe pollution episodes in NCR.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"active\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"}],\\\"evidence\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Evidence\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"\\\"},\\\"stakeholders\\\":[],\\\"globalExamples\\\":[{\\\"country\\\":\\\"China\\\",\\\"policy\\\":\\\"Air Pollution Prevention Action Plan 2013-17\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"PM2.5 reduced by 33% in Beijing within 5 years.\\\",\\\"outcome\\\":\\\"PM2.5 reduced by 33% in Beijing within 5 years.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"WHO\\\"},{\\\"country\\\":\\\"United Kingdom\\\",\\\"policy\\\":\\\"Clean Air Act 1956 \\u0026 Ultra Low Emission Zone\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"London NO2 levels fell 44% in 5 years post-ULEZ.\\\",\\\"outcome\\\":\\\"London NO2 levels fell 44% in 5 years post-ULEZ.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"UK Government\\\"}],\\\"recommendedActions\\\":[{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Implement an Airshed-Based Governance Model\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"MoEFCC, State Governments\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Scale Up Crop Residue Management Infrastructure\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Ministry of Agriculture, State Governments\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Retire Coal Plants Within 5 km of Cities\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Ministry of Power, CEA\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Expand Electric Vehicle Charging Infrastructure\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Ministry of Heavy Industries, DISCOMs\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Universalize LPG Connections for Rural Households\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Ministry of Petroleum, State Governments\\\"]}],\\\"citizenActions\\\":[{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Report Polluting Industries\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Switch to Public Transport\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Install Air Purifiers in Schools\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[]}],\\\"governmentActions\\\":[{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Create Unified Airshed Authority\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"high\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Government\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Double NCAP Budget\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"high\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Government\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Mandate Continuous Emissions Monitoring\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"high\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Government\\\"]}],\\\"metricsToTrack\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Annual PM2.5 Average\\\",\\\"currentValue\\\":\\\"58 µg/m³\\\",\\\"targetValue\\\":\\\"35 µg/m³\\\",\\\"dataSource\\\":\\\"CPCB\\\",\\\"updateFrequency\\\":\\\"\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"NCAP Fund Utilisation\\\",\\\"currentValue\\\":\\\"52%\\\",\\\"targetValue\\\":\\\"90%\\\",\\\"dataSource\\\":\\\"MoEFCC\\\",\\\"updateFrequency\\\":\\\"\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Stubble Burning Incidents\\\",\\\"currentValue\\\":\\\"71,000 (2025)\\\",\\\"targetValue\\\":\\\"10,000 (2028)\\\",\\\"dataSource\\\":\\\"ISRO / Bhuvan\\\",\\\"updateFrequency\\\":\\\"\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"EV Share of New Vehicle Sales\\\",\\\"currentValue\\\":\\\"6.5%\\\",\\\"targetValue\\\":\\\"30% by 2030\\\",\\\"dataSource\\\":\\\"SIAM / VAHAN\\\",\\\"updateFrequency\\\":\\\"\\\"}],\\\"relatedStories\\\":[],\\\"relatedEntities\\\":[]},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"fix-farm-income\\\",\\\"slug\\\":\\\"fix-farm-income\\\",\\\"storySlug\\\":\\\"fix-farm-income\\\",\\\"headline\\\":\\\"Fixing Farm Income: Beyond MSP to a Comprehensive Support System\\\",\\\"summary\\\":\\\"Average monthly income per agricultural household stands at ₹10,200 (NSSO 77th Round). With 86% of farmers owning less than 2 hectares, marginalisation is increasing. Input costs have risen 60% in 5 y\\\",\\\"publishedAt\\\":\\\"2026-05-28T10:00:00Z\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2026-05-28T10:00:00Z\\\",\\\"readingTime\\\":5,\\\"author\\\":{\\\"name\\\":\\\"The Breakdown Editorial\\\"},\\\"evidenceScore\\\":80,\\\"tags\\\":[],\\\"problem\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Average monthly income per agricultural household stands at ₹10,200 (NSSO 77th Round). With 86% of f\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Average monthly income per agricultural household stands at ₹10,200 (NSSO 77th Round). With 86% of farmers owning less than 2 hectares, marginalisation is increasing. Input costs have risen 60% in 5 years while output prices grew only 25%.\\\"},\\\"whoIsAffected\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Who Is Affected\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"\\\"},\\\"rootCauses\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Root Causes\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"(1) Fragmented landholdings — average size declining from 2.3 ha (1970) to 1.08 ha (2025), (2) Input price inflation outpacing output price growth, (3) MSP coverage limited to 23% of crops, (4) Post-harvest losses of 10-15%, (5) Limited access to institutional credit for small farmers, (6) Climate volatility increasing crop failure risk.\\\"},\\\"existingSolutions\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"PM-KISAN\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"₹6,000/year direct income support to all farmer families.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"active\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"GoI\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"MSP Operations\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Government procurement at Minimum Support Price for 23 crops via NAFED/FCI.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"active\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"PM-Fasal Bima Yojana\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Crop insurance with 1.5-2% premium for kharif, 5% for commercial crops.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"active\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"}],\\\"evidence\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Evidence\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"\\\"},\\\"stakeholders\\\":[],\\\"globalExamples\\\":[{\\\"country\\\":\\\"Brazil\\\",\\\"policy\\\":\\\"Family Agriculture Strengthening Program (PRONAF)\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Small farm incomes increased 40% in 10 years.\\\",\\\"outcome\\\":\\\"Small farm incomes increased 40% in 10 years.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"FAO\\\"},{\\\"country\\\":\\\"European Union\\\",\\\"policy\\\":\\\"Common Agricultural Policy Direct Payments\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Farm incomes stabilised within 90% of economy-wide average.\\\",\\\"outcome\\\":\\\"Farm incomes stabilised within 90% of economy-wide average.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"EU Commission\\\"}],\\\"recommendedActions\\\":[{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Expand PM-KISAN to ₹12,000/Year\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Ministry of Finance, Ministry of Agriculture\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Implement Legal MSP Guarantee for Key Crops\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Parliament, Ministry of Agriculture, State Governments\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Scale Farmer Producer Organisations\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"NABARD, SFAC, State Governments\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Post-Harvest Infrastructure Fund\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Ministry of Finance, Ministry of Food Processing\\\"]}],\\\"citizenActions\\\":[{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Join Farmer Producer Organisations\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Adopt Crop Diversification\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[]}],\\\"governmentActions\\\":[{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Pass Farmers' Income Insurance Bill\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"high\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Government\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Double Agriculture Budget\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"high\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Government\\\"]}],\\\"metricsToTrack\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Average Farm Income\\\",\\\"currentValue\\\":\\\"₹10,200/month\\\",\\\"targetValue\\\":\\\"₹20,000/month\\\",\\\"dataSource\\\":\\\"NSSO\\\",\\\"updateFrequency\\\":\\\"\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Farm Household Indebtedness\\\",\\\"currentValue\\\":\\\"52%\\\",\\\"targetValue\\\":\\\"30%\\\",\\\"dataSource\\\":\\\"NSSO\\\",\\\"updateFrequency\\\":\\\"\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"MSP Coverage\\\",\\\"currentValue\\\":\\\"23% crops\\\",\\\"targetValue\\\":\\\"50% crops\\\",\\\"dataSource\\\":\\\"Ministry of Agriculture\\\",\\\"updateFrequency\\\":\\\"\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"PM-KISAN Annual Transfer\\\",\\\"currentValue\\\":\\\"₹6,000\\\",\\\"targetValue\\\":\\\"₹12,000\\\",\\\"dataSource\\\":\\\"DBT Portal\\\",\\\"updateFrequency\\\":\\\"\\\"}],\\\"relatedStories\\\":[],\\\"relatedEntities\\\":[]},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"fix-judicial-pendency\\\",\\\"slug\\\":\\\"fix-judicial-pendency\\\",\\\"storySlug\\\":\\\"fix-judicial-pendency\\\",\\\"headline\\\":\\\"Fixing India's Judicial Pendency: 5 Crore Cases and Counting\\\",\\\"summary\\\":\\\"Over 5 crore cases pending across all levels of judiciary as of June 2026. Supreme Court: 82,000+, High Courts: 60+ lakh, District \\u0026 Subordinate: 4.4+ crore. Average case disposal time: 3-15 years dep\\\",\\\"publishedAt\\\":\\\"2026-05-15T10:00:00Z\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2026-05-15T10:00:00Z\\\",\\\"readingTime\\\":5,\\\"author\\\":{\\\"name\\\":\\\"The Breakdown Editorial\\\"},\\\"evidenceScore\\\":80,\\\"tags\\\":[],\\\"problem\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Over 5 crore cases pending across all levels of judiciary as of June 2026. Supreme Court: 82,000+, H\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Over 5 crore cases pending across all levels of judiciary as of June 2026. Supreme Court: 82,000+, High Courts: 60+ lakh, District \\u0026 Subordinate: 4.4+ crore. Average case disposal time: 3-15 years depending on court type. Judge-to-population ratio stands at 21 judges per million — far below the Law Commission's recommended 50.\\\"},\\\"whoIsAffected\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Who Is Affected\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"\\\"},\\\"rootCauses\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Root Causes\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"(1) Judge vacancies — 30% of High Court positions unfilled, 20% in lower courts, (2) Inadequate infrastructure — 2,000 court halls needed, (3) Low judge-to-population ratio — 21 per million vs global average of 50-60, (4) Procedural inefficiencies — 30+ adjournments average per case, (5) Low technology adoption outside e-Courts project, (6) High vacancy rate in public prosecutors and legal aid counsel.\\\"},\\\"existingSolutions\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"e-Courts Mission Mode Project\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"ICT enablement of courts across India. Phase III (2023-27) with ₹7,000 crore outlay.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"active\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"eCourts.gov.in\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Fast Track Courts\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Special courts for rape, POCSO, and commercial disputes.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"active\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"National Judicial Data Grid\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Real-time pendency data across all courts.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"active\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"}],\\\"evidence\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Evidence\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"\\\"},\\\"stakeholders\\\":[],\\\"globalExamples\\\":[{\\\"country\\\":\\\"Singapore\\\",\\\"policy\\\":\\\"Technology-Mediated Dispute Resolution\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"90% of small claims resolved within 3 months.\\\",\\\"outcome\\\":\\\"90% of small claims resolved within 3 months.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"Singapore Courts\\\"},{\\\"country\\\":\\\"United Kingdom\\\",\\\"policy\\\":\\\"Civil Procedure Rules 1998 \\u0026 Online Dispute Resolution\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Average civil case duration fell from 4 years to 18 months.\\\",\\\"outcome\\\":\\\"Average civil case duration fell from 4 years to 18 months.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"UK Ministry of Justice\\\"}],\\\"recommendedActions\\\":[{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Double Judge Strength to 50 per Million\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Law Ministry, Supreme Court Collegium, State Governments, UPSC\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Budget Allocation to 0.5% of GDP\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Ministry of Finance, Law Ministry\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Mandatory Pre-Litigation Mediation\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Law Commission, Parliament\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"AI-Assisted Case Management System\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"e-Courmittee, NeGD, Law Ministry\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Limit Adjournments to Maximum 3 Per Case\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Parliament, Supreme Court\\\"]}],\\\"citizenActions\\\":[{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Use Plea Bargaining in Appropriate Cases\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Opt for Mediation\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"File Complaints About Judge Vacancies\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[]}],\\\"governmentActions\\\":[{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Create All-India Judicial Service\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"high\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Government\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Pass Judicial Infrastructure Bill\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"high\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"Government\\\"]}],\\\"metricsToTrack\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Judge-to-Population Ratio\\\",\\\"currentValue\\\":\\\"21/million\\\",\\\"targetValue\\\":\\\"50/million\\\",\\\"dataSource\\\":\\\"DoJ Annual Report\\\",\\\"updateFrequency\\\":\\\"\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Case Disposal Time (Average)\\\",\\\"currentValue\\\":\\\"3.7 years\\\",\\\"targetValue\\\":\\\"1 year\\\",\\\"dataSource\\\":\\\"NJDG\\\",\\\"updateFrequency\\\":\\\"\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Judiciary Budget (% of GDP)\\\",\\\"currentValue\\\":\\\"0.12%\\\",\\\"targetValue\\\":\\\"0.5%\\\",\\\"dataSource\\\":\\\"Union Budget\\\",\\\"updateFrequency\\\":\\\"\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Undertrial Prisoners (%)\\\",\\\"currentValue\\\":\\\"65%\\\",\\\"targetValue\\\":\\\"40%\\\",\\\"dataSource\\\":\\\"NCRB Prison Statistics\\\",\\\"updateFrequency\\\":\\\"\\\"}],\\\"relatedStories\\\":[],\\\"relatedEntities\\\":[]},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"fix-anganwadi-reform\\\",\\\"slug\\\":\\\"fix-anganwadi-reform\\\",\\\"storySlug\\\":\\\"fix-anganwadi-reform\\\",\\\"headline\\\":\\\"Fixing India's Anganwadi System: From Nutrition to Empowerment\\\",\\\"summary\\\":\\\"India's 25 lakh anganwadi workers and helpers receive a monthly honorarium of ₹10,000 and ₹5,000 respectively — below the minimum wage in most states. They have no pension, health insurance, or paid l\\\",\\\"publishedAt\\\":\\\"2026-07-30T06:00:00Z\\\",\\\"updatedAt\\\":\\\"2026-07-30T06:00:00Z\\\",\\\"readingTime\\\":5,\\\"author\\\":{\\\"name\\\":\\\"The Breakdown Editorial\\\"},\\\"evidenceScore\\\":80,\\\"tags\\\":[],\\\"problem\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"India's 25 lakh anganwadi workers and helpers receive a monthly honorarium of ₹10,000 and ₹5,000 res\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"India's 25 lakh anganwadi workers and helpers receive a monthly honorarium of ₹10,000 and ₹5,000 respectively — below the minimum wage in most states. They have no pension, health insurance, or paid leave. Despite managing nutrition, pre-school education, and health tracking for 10 crore beneficiaries, they are classified as \\\\\\\"volunteers\\\\\\\" rather than government employees.\\\"},\\\"whoIsAffected\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Who Is Affected\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"\\\"},\\\"rootCauses\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Root Causes\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Three structural issues: (1) Workers are classified as \\\\\\\"honorary\\\\\\\" volunteers rather than employees, excluding them from labour protections, (2) ICDS funding is split across centre (60%), state (40%) with no dedicated infrastructure maintenance budget, (3) No centralised monitoring of anganwadi infrastructure — CAG found 40% of centres lack basic amenities but there is no penalty for state non-compliance.\\\"},\\\"existingSolutions\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"ICDS-CAS (Common Application Software)\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Smartphone-based real-time nutrition tracking and attendance system rolled out to all centres.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"active\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"MWCD\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"POSHAN Abhiyaan\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"National Nutrition Mission with targeted stunting reduction goals and inter-sectoral convergence.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"active\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"State-Level Honorarium Revisions\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Some states (Kerala, Tamil Nadu, Karnataka) have supplemented central honorarium with state contributions.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"active\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"}],\\\"evidence\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Evidence\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"\\\"},\\\"stakeholders\\\":[],\\\"globalExamples\\\":[{\\\"country\\\":\\\"Brazil\\\",\\\"policy\\\":\\\"Bolsa Família conditional cash transfers\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Stunting reduced from 37% to 7% in 20 years; frontline workers earn 2x minimum wage.\\\",\\\"outcome\\\":\\\"Stunting reduced from 37% to 7% in 20 years; frontline workers earn 2x minimum wage.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"World Bank\\\"},{\\\"country\\\":\\\"Thailand\\\",\\\"policy\\\":\\\"Community-Based Nutrition Programme\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Thailand eliminated severe malnutrition by 2005 and achieved universal health coverage.\\\",\\\"outcome\\\":\\\"Thailand eliminated severe malnutrition by 2005 and achieved universal health coverage.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"WHO\\\"},{\\\"country\\\":\\\"Chile\\\",\\\"policy\\\":\\\"Chile Crece Contigo\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Developmental delays reduced 30% in high-priority areas within 5 years.\\\",\\\"outcome\\\":\\\"Developmental delays reduced 30% in high-priority areas within 5 years.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"UNICEF\\\"}],\\\"recommendedActions\\\":[{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Grant Employee Status to Anganwadi Workers\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"MWCD, Ministry of Labour, Ministry of Finance\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Create Infrastructure Maintenance Fund\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"MWCD, Ministry of Finance, State Governments\\\"]},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Reduce Worker-to-Centre Ratio\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"timeframe\\\":\\\"medium-term\\\",\\\"actors\\\":[\\\"M